---
alwaysApply: true
---
documentation:
  userFacingFeatureChanges:
    description: "When you make a change that adds, removes, or significantly alters a user-facing feature (symptoms, AI tools, appointment directory, admin UI, clinical review), you must also update the relevant documentation files."
    requiredActions:
      - checkAndUpdate:
          files:
            - "docs-site/pages/ (the relevant feature/getting-started/governance page)"
            - "/README.md"
          instruction: "Review and update any affected sections to reflect the change"
      - updateReleaseNotes:
          file: "docs-site/pages/release-notes.mdx"
          instruction: "Add the user-visible change under the appropriate section (New / Updated / Fixed / For system administrators) and bump the version banner on docs-site/pages/index.mdx"
          format: "Brief description of the change"
    userFacingFeatures:
      - symptoms
      - aiTools
      - appointmentDirectory
      - adminUI
      - clinicalReview
    examples:
      - "Adding a new symptom filter"
      - "Modifying the AI instruction editor UI"
      - "Changing appointment directory functionality"
      - "Updating admin dashboard layout"
      - "Altering clinical review workflow"
